[[VLANs|VLAN]] are a [[Switching]] technology that operates at [[Layer 2|Datalink Layer]].

[[VLANs|VLAN]] provide a [[Layer 2|Datalink Layer]] boundry - so in order for two devices on different [[VLANs|VLAN]] to communicate, they need a [[Layer 3|Network Layer]] protocol. Typically they do so through the [[Default Gateway]].